body:
@jdalton 

Sorry this is my first time really doing any kind of performance re-write like this...or diving into source code for that matter; I also apologize for this not being really where I should have reopened an issue. I just figured for continuity of the question asked it was best asked here.

I first swapped out, I guess you would call it _modules_, and went with:

```javascript
import throttle from 'lodash-es/throttle';
```

This led to about a 100kb reduction, a good start.

 I then looked at the `babel-plugin-lodash` and for starters am just running it in `development` mode in my `.babelrc`:

```rc
{
  "env": {
    "development": {
      "presets": ["env", ["es2015", {"modules": false}], "react", "stage-0"],
      "plugins": [
        "lodash",
        "transform-class-properties",
        "react-hot-loader/babel"
      ]
    },
    "production": {
      "presets": [["es2015", {"modules": false}], "react", "stage-0"]
    },
    "test": {
      "presets": ["env", ["es2015", {"modules": false}], "react", "stage-0"],
      "plugins": ["istanbul"]
    }
  }
}
```
My question for the plugin refers to the _optionsObject_:
```rc
 ["lodash", { "id": "lodash-es", cwd: "???" }],
```
I'm a little unsure what is required in the _current working directory_ key. Is that possibly the location of the lodash method being used in my code, or is that the path to `lodash-es`? The name being `cwd` I feel the latter is probably not right.

My other question is about `lodash-webpack-plugin`:

I looked at the _mapping.js_ file to see what the feature would be for _throttle_ and did not find it so I originally just went with using `"lodash"` in the `.babelrc` & using `new LodashModuleReplacementPlugin(),` in my `webpack.dev.config.js`. I was meet with about a 24kb reduction in `lodash@4.17.4` (I used `webpack-dashboard` to get a break down of the modules):

_webpack.dev.config.js_
```javascript 
require('dotenv-safe').load();

const webpack = require('webpack');
const path = require('path');
const ExtractTextPlugin = require('extract-text-webpack-plugin');
const HtmlWebpackPlugin = require('html-webpack-plugin');
const DashboardPlugin = require('webpack-dashboard/plugin');
const LodashModuleReplacementPlugin = require('lodash-webpack-plugin');

const VENDOR_LIBS = [
  'axios', 'lodash-es', 'react', 'react-dom', 'react-redux',
  'react-redux-multilingual', 'react-redux-toastr', 'react-router',
  'react-router-redux', 'redux', 'redux-auth-wrapper',
  'redux-form', 'redux-pack', 'redux-promise-middleware',
  'semantic-ui-react'
];

module.exports = {
  entry: {
    bundle: [
      'babel-polyfill',
      'react-hot-loader/patch',
      'webpack-dev-server/client?http://localhost:9000',
      'webpack/hot/only-dev-server',
      './client/index.js'
    ],
    vendor: VENDOR_LIBS,
  },
  output: {
    path: path.join(__dirname, 'dist'),
    filename: '[name].js',
    publicPath: '/'
  },
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        use: 'babel-loader',
        test: /\.js$/,
        exclude: /node_modules/,
      },
      {
        loader: ExtractTextPlugin.extract({
          loader: 'css-loader'
        }),
        test: /\.css$/
      }
    ]
  },
  performance: {
    hints: false
  },
  devtool: 'inline-source-map',
  devServer: {
    contentBase: path.join(__dirname, 'dist'),
    compress: true,
    port: 9000,
    hot: true,
    inline: true,
    historyApiFallback: true,
    open: true,
    quiet: true,
    proxy: {
      '/api': 'http://localhost:3000'
    }
  },
  plugins: [
    new LodashModuleReplacementPlugin(),
    new webpack.DefinePlugin({
      'process.env': {
        NODE_ENV: JSON.stringify(process.env.NODE_ENV),
        CLOUD_NAME: JSON.stringify(process.env.CLOUD_NAME),
        UPLOAD_PRESET: JSON.stringify(process.env.UPLOAD_PRESET),
      }
    }),
    new webpack.optimize.CommonsChunkPlugin({
      names: ['vendor', 'manifest']
    }),
    new DashboardPlugin(),
    new HtmlWebpackPlugin({
      template: 'public/index.html'
    }),
    new webpack.HotModuleReplacementPlugin(),
    new webpack.NamedModulesPlugin(),
    new ExtractTextPlugin('style.css'),
  ]
};
```

I do get an interesting error message when adding `new LodashModuleReplacementPlugin(),`:

![screen shot 2017-01-24 at 11 20 21 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/19720404/22278860/314da926-e28c-11e6-8746-04ceb13d2df6.png)

It's only when this new instance is declared that the error appears; but it seems to be breaking something in my store (probably the _throttle_) and thus causes any `connect()` components to fail with this error message. However when I looked at the source code for the `lodash-es/throttle` method I did not see anything referring to an _iteratee_ that could some how be getting passed as a prop. It very well could correlate as well to not passing the `cwd` key in the `.babelrc`.

Any guidance or explanation to my questions would be greatly appreciated. The error could likely be conflict with different techs and I will have to dive in to find that fix. Thanks!
